We recommended that Management:
Direct the Municipal Budget Officer (MBO) and Municipal Treasurer review their income targets for Community Tax- Corporation and Inspection Fees which reported zero collections for CYs 2018 and 2019;
Direct the Municipal Treasurer to exclude the income from operations of Oas Community College from locally sourced income and instead, should be classified as income from external sources;
Require the MBO and Municipal Treasurer to carefully review and assess their revenue projections for each income account to ensure systematic and realistic forecasting of revenue collections for the ensuing year; and
Thereafter, require the Municipal Treasurer to conduct periodic review and take the necessary actions to ensure collection targets are attained and collection efficiency is improved.

We recommended that Management:
Require the HRMO to formulate a Human Resource Plan and issue a uniform policy guidelines on the hiring of JO personnel to appropriately determine the necessity of the hiring thereof and as well as to strengthen internal controls pertaining thereto;
Reduce/limit hiring of JOs and instead fill up vacant plantilla positions in the LGU;
Evaluate and determine the appropriate personnel complement of each office/department in the Municipal Government and effect the necessary amendments in their respective plantilla, if warranted.

