We reiterated our prior year’s recommendations and emphasize that Management:

Strictly observe the requirements on complete documentation to support the disbursement;

Discontinue the irregular practice of granting Cash Advance for travel to the Disbursing Officer for reimbursement of travel expenses of various employees, which warrant the issuance of audit disallowance, instead individual check be issued to employee granted with Cash Advance for Travel;

Stop the use of general terms in describing the purpose of Cash Advance, but instead indicate the specific purpose for which the Cash Advance were granted;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to stop the practice or allowing in pre-audit the granting of additional Cash Advances to officials and employees who have unsettled Cash Advances, since it is the Municipal Accountant who certifies that the official or employee has no previous Cash Advances. Inability to comply will result to being one of the persons liable or responsible on audit disallowances/suspensions relative to the granting of Cash Advances; and

Impose adherence by officials and employees on the use of Cash Advance for which it was granted.

We recommended that the Management:

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to properly check claims of all officials/employees for seminars / conferences and exclude the per diems of those whose registration fees and hotel bills cover meal allowance as well as other excess claims;

Require the refund of excess per diem and other travel expenses collected by the concerned officials and employees as well as the submission of the required supporting documents, otherwise this warrant the issuance of audit disallowance and suspension.

